Anyone who has seen Tommy Rando perform already knows what the rest of the world is about to discover. Tommy's songs are strong and individual; however, the first thing that captures your attention is the unique tone of his voice which has a warm and husky texture. Even his soulful whisper conveys power, conviction and grace - all the cuts and bruises of a life fully lived. When he lets rip, we see his emotion creep in like an approaching storm.

Rando, an Australian singer-songwriter, was helped along by a scholarship grant to the National Guitar Summer Workshop held in Connecticut, New York.

It was there that Tommy was guided to seek out the ingredients that shaped his artistic style. Following his time in New York, Tommy toured the US for BMI hooking up with industry greats such as Jeff Cohen, Seymore Stein and ex-manager to Elton John, John Reid.

Back at home, Tommy has played with Australia's best including: "Taxiride", "Boomcrash Opera" and "Invertigo". He has written songs for Vanessa Amorosi, Lee Harding, Alan Fletcher and Kirsty Crawford to name just a few. With a growing catalogue, Tommy has his tunes playing regularly on the television show "Neighbours" as well as co-writing the number one ARIA hit "Wasabi" for Australian Idol's Lee Harding.

Early inspiration came from artists such as Jimi Hendrix, Steve Ray Vaughan, The Beatles, Jeff Buckley, Elton John, Cats Stevens, Joni Mitchell, John Hiatt, Miles Davis, Radiohead, The Dave Matthews Band, soul, blues and gospel singers. 

There is no doubt that anyone in the audience of one of Tommy's shows will see a brilliant singer/songwriter who truly wears his heart on his sleeve. His ageless songs are executed with vision and clarity and delivered with heart-felt reflection and passion.

Otto von Ruggins, self-proclaimed Master of the Unheard Øf, was born on the 24th of July on a leap year, so his birthday is really July 25th (Christmas In July). His first experience of rock'n'roll was watching the Dick Clark countdown on Friday nights with his older sister. Seeing Jerry Lee Lewis banging the piano and his stage performance made him want to make music, so he took piano lessons, but stopped ‘til The Beatles showed up playing their own instruments. It was probably The Dave Clark Five that inspired him to close his savings account and buy a Vox Continental Organ. Otto's first band was 'From Down Under' (no relation to the land of Oz, as he was expressing the concept of 'underground' before there was one). They played original songs and a repertoire that included early Animals, Who, Yardbirds, Them and Small Faces. What followed next was 'Christmas In July' (he really isn't an egomaniac). His first encounter with VON LMO was at the Village Theater where VON announced that he had just challenged Keith Moon to a drum battle. Otto got backstage and this was confirmed when The Vagrants' drummer said some crazy guy had indeed laid down the gauntlet. Soon after, VON LMO encountered Otto chasing a butterfly without a net. Next came 'Funeral of Art', with VON on drums and a concept of getting the 1% to donate their ‘worthless’ art to be burned onstage, but when that didn't work, Otto conceived of the band playing inside a giant computerized box with cameras projecting their performance onto large screens - before it was technologically possible. Always ahead of the times, these futuristic plans were a foreshadowing of what is now termed Steampunk. Otto & VON went off to England, following the path of Jimi Hendrix. They recorded demos with an ex-Procol Harum bassist, but couldn't get signed and VON & Otto went in different directions when they returned to NY. Otto first played synthesizer at Shea Stadium during the Avant Garde Festival in 1974. His sounds attracted such crowds that he describes the effect as feeding pigeons. By the mid-70s, VON LMO & Otto were back together in 'Kongress'. A first gig at CBGBs generated a review in Variety - "Kongress is a band who expect a lot of auditors." Then the IRS audited Otto." Soon, it was off to Max's Kansas City, where booking impresario Peter Crowley introduced Otto to pictures of Geoffrey Crozier who really was a Madgician from Oz. They jammed together w/ Geoffrey, but VON went home, broke his leg & was not there at Max's for a first gig w/ Geoffrey, which Peter claimed nobody could have followed - not even Kiss or Alice Cooper - and crowd response was better than for the NY Dolls. Punk Magazine dubbed them, “The most dangerous band in the world.”  Otto then got together w/ Kongress guitarist Robert Crash & put out an EP, 'Movie Viewers', which came w/ 4D glasses & a double groove. It came back full circle w/ Otto von Ruggins & VON LMO together again in the 21st Century, as the ultimate Cosmic Rock duo, AVANT DUEL, unleashing a masterpiece in 2012 - BEYOND HUMAN. Hello Music declared that AVANT DUEL is "...on the cusp of greatness" and their "music is its own art form" with comparisons to Daft Punk & Kraftwerk. Otto's latest release had seeds sown back in the early '90s when he was troublemaker in chief on The Morton Downey, Jr. Show advocating to legalize cannabis over 30 years ago before it became fashionable. His single, released on Election Day 2020 - The Ugly American - is an Anthem for the Moment by Kongress, featuring Phil Faconti on Screaming Guitar & Dave Eggar on Heroic Electric Cello. The Kollagescopic Video can be seen @ youtube.com/ottovr Closed Caption (CC) for lyrics/use earbuds for 'manipulated' voices. Just added new single - Running With The Wolves by Kongress ft. Sky Saxon - Youtube video @ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wGMnwUXys7I Closed Caption (CC) for lyrics.

Petite:Unique Records … LAUNCH: 1 April 2010

Wir sind entzückt! – denn das exquisit-Musiklabel Petite:Unique Records ist geboren. War alles schon da? Nicht doch. Petite:Unique vereint in seinem Credo Sammleranspruch und Originale reinster Tonfreude.

Verantwortlich für diesen aparten Zuwachs im Musikbasar ist die Japanisch-Deutsch-Englisch sprechlustige, PR-gewandte Mrs P:etite. Nach umfassenden Studien der Label und Verlags-Praxis im Herzen Londons und Hamburgs, einer knallharten Ausbildung in Music-Plugging-Gepflogenheiten in den Räumen der BBC-Radios & der Entwicklung eines empörenden Merchandise-Scharfsinns, war es nun an der Zeit, Petite:Unique Records Leben einzu- hauchen und alle gesammelten Fertigkeiten darin zu bündeln.

Schon im Mai 2010 serviert Mrs P:etite den ersten Petite:Unique Leckerbissen. Ambient-Minimalist udosson veröffentlicht sein Debüt in 2 (!) exklusiven & limitierten Sammler- editionen. Gespannt? Nun, Vorfreude ist die schönste Freude!

Stehenden Fußes folgt im September 2010 September Leaves mit seinem neuen Werk, ebenfalls in höchst individueller Sammlerherz-Ausgabe. Wenn jetzt die Ohren und Kennerhändchen nicht vor neugieriger Euphorie ganz heiß werden …

His name was borrowed from a famous track on Prince’s “Purple Rain” album, an album of vertiginous music and lyrics full of explicit seductive and erotic references. The cherry picked “verbal sampling” offers exquisite musical shivers and an eclectic appeal. With an unmistakable mighty effectiveness, devilish catchiness, Darlin’Nikki’s sound adorns itself with a few acid or “trancy” overtones and other rock’n roll reminiscences still relevant to our time. All going from unforeseeable patterns, inexorable breaks, and from gliding to groovy gems, all wrapped in a high tech cloth. Portrayed as a rising value on the Breton electro scene and even as a “Breizh touch” flag bearer by specialized press, Darlin Nikki is a perfect example of an ingenious electronic musical project, well anchored in its time. Darlin’ Nikki (who’s not a twosome anymore) has very much listened and absorbed different music styles, and has entirely earned his place within the new French electro generation. Enhanced by 3 promising EP (version 3.3, we are one and panic), he delivers such a blast on stage that no pair of legs or bums can resist. Darlin’ Nikki has already performed at the Astropolis festival (Brest, France) in 2004, the Transmusicales festival (Rennes, France) in 2006, the Rex club (Paris) and in many other venues all over France.

Founded in late 2001, Offshore Recordings exists to further the sounds of leftfield drum and bass. Very few labels take the time to explore the possibilities within the genre, but Offshore hopes to add some forward-thinking sounds to everyone’s DJ bag/record crate.

Having begun as an outlet to release the work of Anemone and Clever, the label took on a broader spectrum, when Clever took the helm. The roster now includes- Alaska, Alpha Omega, Anemone, ASC, Clever, Deep Blue, Endemic Void, Fanu, Fracture + Neptune, Graphic, Intex Systems, Justice, Macc, Marstman, Nucleus, Paradox, Pieter K, Seba, Sileni and Tundra with remixes from Klute, Martyn, Nubian Mindz, Omni Trio, Titonton, LXC, Starkey and Vex’d.

The label has gained recognition for both its originality and boundary pushing, by both the press and the scene. Projects with Ohm Resistance, Commercial Suicide and Hotflush have encouraged this. The ethics behind the label have fans comparing it to such greats as Partisan and Certificate 18.

Expect only great things from this Brooklyn based outfit, whose future becomes brighter and brighter everyday.

BIO:
With the value granted by experience, M.E.M.O. is as versatile as he is elegant. The native of Malaga recently awarded as best Deep House artist at the Hispano- American Vicious Music Awards 2018, and he harmonizes talent and technical skills with a suggestivetendency to risk and a natural predisposition to theavant-garde. This will has run through his veins since he was a child, and when he became a teenager he combined his piano studies with his role as a singer and guitarist in a band halfway between rap and metal. A couple of years later, with the arrival of the sounds imported from UK and Germany to Andalusia, electronic music burst into his life and being still very young, he is playing in Festivals for more than 20,000 people, turned from the beginning into a reference within the scene.
​
Soon Andalusia is too small for the aspirations of M.E.M.O. who, inevitably, begins his journey through other cities and countries. First he settled in Barcelona, where he opened his own vinyl shop and performed at the main clubs in the city such as Moog, Fellini, Catwalk and had a residency at the party ZEN at City Hall which he combined with another residency at the club in London, 54. Later on he moved toIbiza for ve years, where he leaves his mark with regularperformances at Space, Privilege and Sankeys, amongst others. A career of more than 22 years that has taken himto major festivals such as Cream elds, Dreambeach orWinter Music Conference, playing many countries where
he has been able to demonstrate his skills: Germany,England, Norway, France, Netherlands, Egypt, Russia,Croatia, USA, Mexico...
​
And all of this without mentioning his facet as a producer,because in this territory, M.E.M.O. also excels. His workswith Pig & Dan “All U Need” on Yoshitoshi Records and“Vicking Princess” on Bedrock Records, are importantexamples of this, which have been recognized. “Tai Tai”, edited by the Berlin label Mobilee Records, Best Seller Deep House 2018 and its presence in Beatport’s Top 100 Deep House for more than 4 months, reaching number 3. Its second and recently released on Mobilee “Another Night“ receives like the previous support of greats likeJohn Digweed, Tiësto or Pete Tong among others, which is presented several times on BBC Radio1, these releases and his frequent appearances in the showcase of the seal consecrate this artist from Malaga in the German label.
​
But, this is not the end of his biography, those whoknow him can see that the trajectory of M.E.M.O. is morealive than ever. Currently, in addition to his DJ sets, he is immersed in his new Live Act, which premiered atWatergate in Berlin and has already made famous tours and festivals with this format, an area he combines withhis work at Pure Ibiza Radio, where It has a weekly spacefull of feeling and freedom.

Warboy produces cutting-edge projects that galvanise people to explore and celebrate identity, sexuality, and diversity.

He has been a cultural provocateur at the forefront of creative and social activism for three decades and is an influential figure in London’s club culture with DJ Mag observing that he ‘remains one of alternative clubland’s greatest forces who is constantly ahead of the curve’.

His diverse portfolio of club nights range from the large scale Sabajaq techno events to anarchic nu-rave warehouse parties All You Can Eat, to weekly disco debauchery with Caligula, curating underground events, and hosting London Fashion Week parties.

He has been a key member in the team responsible for developing nightclub Egg London’s transformative new direction, landing DJ Mag's Best of British award for 'Best Large Club' 2017 and inclusion in DJ Mag’s Top 100 Clubs internationally for the three consecutive years. 

Other pioneering collaborations include a clothing collection, with Machine-A founder Stavros Karelis, that inspired the look of an East London generation clad in black and launching an online TV channel, AYCE.TV, in 2006 during the infancy of online and social media.

His consultancy work for high profile clients includes Harper’s Bazaar, BBC Panorama, London Fashion Week, Britain’s Next Top Model, Don’t Panic, and most recently an advisory role on Smirnoff’s TV and print campaign celebrating genderqueer and non-binary identities.

As part of the early 90s queer movement, he worked in the LGTBQ press and was involved in direct action organisations OutRage!, Act-Up, and GMFA.

I feel like my transport should be an extension of my personality. And this is like my little window to the world... and every minute's a different show. I may not understand it. I may not even necessarily agree with it. But I'll tell you what I've accepted: just sort of glide along. You want to keep things on an even key, this is what I'm saying. You want to go with the flow. The sea refuses no river. The idea is to remain in a state of constant departure whilst always arriving. It saves on introductions and goodbyes. The ride does not require explanation - just occupants. That's where you guys come in. It's like you come onto this planet with a crayon box. Now you may get the 8 pack, you may get the 16 pack but it's all in what you do with the crayons - the colors - that you're given. Don't worry about colouring within the lines or colouring outside the lines - I say colour outside the lines, you know what I mean? Colour all over the page; don't box me in! We're in motion to the ocean.

friedrich glorian has been into music since the mid 60s with local rock bands, and started off a serious musical career as lead guitar player with the 70s german prog rock band Prof. Wolfff (one of the first rock bands in germany to use german lyrics). studies at the jazz school munich (1975-77), training in north indian vocal music and percussion (dhrupad style), 1982-88 in india, provided a wide experience in rock, fusion, world, experimental, electronic, and also with dance and theater projects. he had the opportunity to explore and practice sound healing, teach workshops and training courses mainly in europe, but also for a short period in ethiopia.

at present he composes music for contemporary and multimedia music/dance projects, performs his music live on electric guzheng and percussion (postworld improvised music/live looping/fx), and with multimedia musicdance projects. he facilitates circledrumevents (community/corporate drumming) and proposes innerSounds relaxation/healing concerts on tibetan bowls and gongs.

Chris Rossi A.K.A Aquilaganja/Drop the Junk hails from a small town on the outskirts of Glasgow, Scotland called Milngavie. At a young age Chris got into the hardcore scene which was the dominant music style in Glasgow and Scotland at the time, respecting artists such as Marc Smith, Scott Brown & Lenny Dee to name a few.

Electronic dance music has always been a passion of Chris’s no matter what the genre though the first styles he chose to mix on vinyl were Hard House and Hardstyle.

After a few years mixing on vinyl Chris decided the next best thing to look into was Dance Music Production courses at the School of Sound Recordings in Manchester, England which is owned and run but Ian Ho, who was the main producer/audio engineer for classic dance group N-Trance. Chris chose to do an advanced Cubase course which saw him score top marks in his class by the end of the course.

As soon as Chris finished his production course he got in contact with the legendary Dj/Producer Alex Calver (Calvertron) who Chris highly respected for his unique style and his ability to write multiple genres at a professional level. This gave Chris the perfect opportunity over a 2-3 year period to learn tricks of the trade production wise from his ideal which was to boost Chris’s own ability in the studio.

Mid 2008 saw Chris launch his Aquilaganja alias writing Electro/House and a little bit of Minimal/Techno. By writing these genres Chris managed to get his tracks signed to labels such as:

Born in Montreal, Canada, Nitrous (also know as D-Joos) grew up listening to a wide range of different music (Hip-Hop, Metal, Grunge, Punk, Rock). He was first exposed to electronic music in the early 90's through the now infamous Goldie track, Inner City Life. This is where everything changed for him, slowly starting buying vinyls and first spinning House and Techno music. He later made the big switch and started spinning exclusively Drum and Bass. In 1999, he created his own production company called “Kracked Knuckles”, doing small and intimate dnb events in Montreal. Resident DJ and Promoter for Uber/Body People, Birmingham, now residing in Sydney, Australia.

Heavily influenced by Soul, Funk, Disco and Hip Hop from a young age, Gary began Djing in 1996 and since playing one of his first gigs for renowned club night, Miss Moneypenny’s aged just 17, he has been a regular on the Birmingham club scene playing at most of the city’s club nights and venues. 

In 2000 He won the Miss Moneypenny’s DJ of the Year Competition beating many established local DJ’s to win the prize of playing Miss Moneypenny’s Closing Party at El Divino, Ibiza alongside Danny Rampling. In 2001, he was selected as the first UK DJ to be invited to join the Estonian based Macadam Music Agency Estonia and was regularly playing in Estonia, as well as holding a bi-monthly residency for the Flyaway parties in Naples. In 2003, he became resident for the prestigious ”Rouge” and "Babooshka" nights in Birmingham where he played alongside names such as Roger Sanchez, Derrick Carter, David Morales, Tim Deluxe & Jocelyn Brown

In 2007, Gary teamed up with his close friend Charlie John to create the much loved ”Days Like This" parties at Red Bar in Birmingham which ran for over 3 years and regularly featured guests such as DJ Spen, Karizma, Alix Alvarez, Rocco, Ralf Gum, Yass, Zed Bias, Reelsoul, Aaron Ross, Neil Pierce, Phil Asher, Sean Mccabe, Groove Assassin, all in an intimate 100 capacity setting.

Gary has regularly played across the UK and Europe and has featured at a number of high profile club nights and venues including Ministry Of Sound, Le Queen (Paris), Prive (Talinn), El Divino (Ibiza), Cafe Mambo (Ibiza), Il Ciclope (Naples), Thompsons Garage (Belfast) & Mecca (Prague) and events such as the Soul Village Weekender and a residency at the Vocal Booth Weekender in Spain.

Prior to moving to Sydney, he promoted the Uber parties in Birmingham which brought Birmingham debuts for the likes of Detroit Swindle, Max Graef, Jimpster, Atjazz, Rahaan, Franck Roger, Andre Lodemann, Halo, Shur-I-Kan, Opolopo, Lay-far, Frankie Feliciano, Thatmanmonkz as well as co-promoting parties playing alongside the likes of Louie Vega, Kenny Dope, Jazzanova, Greg Wilson.

During his time in Sydney, he's been heavily involved in the Big Fun parties as well as playing for the likes of S.A.S.H, Rotary Disco, Slyfox, Flinders and Stanleys

I love tight production and hard-to-categorize styles. While there are genres of music that I particularly like, when it comes to me and my music, genres collide to form tracks that collectively define what I hear as an evolving and ambitious sound.

My first official releases were under the name Totemplow (1996-2001) and were mostly guitar-oriented experimental ambient excursions, although I did get into sampling near the end of it. Some of my favorite press described Totemplow as "one of the deepest (as in depth charges) mixes around” (Andrew Bartlett/The Stranger) and "inspired ritualist on a journey through strange musical topographies" (Marc Kate)

In the early 1990’s I played guitar and sang in a couple of psychedelic grunge bands in my hometown of Seattle. Those bands were Longbottom Weed (1989-91) and Shiva (1991-94).

Fhernando is a globally-acclaimed Internet EDM artist and music producer whose music can be heard from the cafes of Madrid to the media commercials of Greece and Morocco. He presents listeners with a unique style of EDM, one that’s influenced by his own Latin culture. His latest album, All I Have, was composed in Paris and has received an overwhelmingly positive reception from the online music community.

Fhernando has been making original music since the late 90s but has only been putting music out commercially since 2008. His album Last Days Of Disco has been downloaded over 200,000 times on platforms like Jamendo and Frostclick and had tracks used in advertising and other creative projects in several European countries. His next album, Crazy Sexy Funky Love, also did very well and had tracks placed on several label compilations.

Fhernando has big goals for his music career and he has the block-rockin’ beats and powerful hooks needed to make those goals happen. He is a fresh sound in an overcrowded playing field, which gets him a lot of attention. Is he the future of EDM? It’s too soon to tell but anyone interested in the answer to that question needs a Fhernando playlist in their life today.

Slovak formation Ear Drum Kru was founded in 1996 as an experimental project of three DJs and programmer Michal Iliaš, "marked by" RAVE craze early 90's, especially bands like The Prodigy, Altern 8, Human Resurce, SL2, The Shamen, Moby and KLF. In the period 1995-2000 EDK organized parties of all kinds electronic-dance-music, which was great inspiration for making of their own music. They released the first Slovak Drum&Bass vinyl in 2000. Today EDK consists of Miro "Base" Guzma, Majo "Loggo" Miklosko, Matej "DiBonboni" Daubner and Peter "Hary" Kolla. Their taste in music was always varied and so is the creation of the band, which often shows in their DJ sets aka EDK Sound System. Their latests flavours are electro, breakbeat, techno and acid.

Bio
	
Soy DJ, sí, mezclo discos de otra gente, uno atrás de otro y desde cierto punto de vista creo algo desconocido. Es posible que eso nuevo que ocasiono sea una sensación abismal, te hago caer, en lo más profundo del panocéano musical, esa gran masa dividida por géneros muy diferenciados por sus exóticos rasgos y secretos que esconden; entre ellos figura, la vasta y variada topografía del drum & bass. Es en este aspecto, donde este gran abismo cala el interés humano, y mi intención es ayudarte a descubrirlo, hasta llegar al asombro.

/////////////////////////

Pioneer of the Drum and Bass movement of South America, Eduardo LaForgia, just like Tim Roth in Reservoir Dogs was baptized Orange. With time his he was dubbed the Bad Boy of Buenos Aires, as he refused to play the "good boy" and injected local dancefloors with the down and dirty basslines of jungle in the 90's when house and techno were the mainstream. Today he continues to fight the current, keeping locals up to date on the most avant-garde of contemporary Drum and Bass and gaining international fame for his long running party +160 with its constant showcase of the best Djs on the scene. He's been mackin the dj booth since he was 16, and today his experience shows. His faithful devotion has to the Bass Music is a godsend to the genre and a blessing to those who habitat his dancefloor.

After many sleepless nights dancing to the house and techno house sounds of the mid 90’s, Julien fell under the spell of masterful DJ’s like Richie Hawtin, Derrick May and Derrick Carter. Late nights were all about dancing and listening to the techniques, programing and mixing styles of the experienced DJ. At the age of 17, Julien started making mix tapes for friends. The early mix tapes led to dj sets at house parties and one off events, which eventually opened the doors to Julien’s first club gig.

A true DJ at heart and in the soul, Julien began making waves in his home city with residencies at the world-renowned Guvernment and Toronto after hours favorite, Comfort Zone. His selected blend of house, techno and minimal music combined with a magnetic charisma behind the decks, has moved dance floors from New York to Ibiza, Mexico to Miami, and beyond. 
﻿ 
In 2008, Julien was invited to play at the 1st Annual BPM Festival in Playa Del Carmen, Mexico, where a memorable set at Kool Beach Club has led to a 9 year running residency. Julien has warmed up the stage for underground's best DJ's such as Richie Hawtin, Marco Carola and Dubfire. In 2012 Julien made his Ibiza debut at Sankey’s and played New York’s Electric Zoo Festival, a three-day event that had more than 110,000 partygoers in attendance. 
﻿ 
Wanting to be closer to the music and the production process, Julien attended the Producing/Engineering program at Harris Institute for The Arts in Toronto. During that time he spent hours in the studio experimenting with, sound, synthesizers, drum machines and hardware effects. 
The first tracks were bootlegs and white label remix’s, including a remix of Boris Dlugosch’s “Keep Pushin”. In 2008, Julien began creating and releasing original dance floor oriented house and techno with a vibe and style that draws from those experiences and emotions of a good underground party. 
​ 
Julien’s discography includes music released on international imprints such as Rawthentic, Inmotion, Serkal, Potobollo, Proper Musique, Zeitlos, Restructured and Pins and Needles. His tracks have been played and supported by global DJ’s and have appeared on various charts including the globally competitive Beatport Top 100.

After 12 years in the game, Kissy Sell Out continues to be one of the most influential and globally respected names of the British dance music industry. With fresh projects evolving in 2018 as the label manager of Stepper Man and Lengoland, his bass house productions and world-class DJ mixing talents have forged the start of a second chapter in his vibrant and prestigious career. 

With his critically-acclaimed new album as KSO called “Style From The Westside” – described by UKF as “the realest bassline album you’ll hear all year” – Kissy has used his wealth of experience to shred up every old habit and signature sound he has honed in the past and re-written the rule book of electronic music production yet again. 

The list of collaborators featuring on the album reads like a who’s who of heavy-hitters in the current bassline and bass house scenes; including DJ Q, Darkzy, Dread MC, Pavv, JG, Tengu, Sam Supplier, J69, Jaikea, and The Wideboys. 

KSO’s lists of achievements in the music industry and public-eye are as long as they are astounding. He started at the tender age of 21 working on official game-changing remixes for A-list pop-stars such as Mark Ronson, Calvin Harris and Gwen Stefani (all while he was still at London’s Central Saint Martins art college), and went on to find success across the globe as an influential taste-maker at BBC Radio 1, global brand ambassador for Pioneer DJ, regular tour support act for The Prodigy and Fatboy Slim, as well as a unique music industry personality and public figure who can claim to have debated against Stephen Fry at Cambridge University and composed official music for the 2012 London Olympics ceremonies in Trafalgar Square and Buckingham Palace.

For lovers of lower frequencies

I'm primarily a house music DJ because that's what I enjoy playing most nowadays but I'm a music lover above all so I can't help listening to almost every other EDM genre regularly at home and sometimes playing other music styles when the place and the crowd demand it.

I started djing electronic music in the 90s when I discovered EDM and fell in love with almost all the different flavors that were growing fast at the time like D&B, breakbeat, house, techno, electro, downtempo, trip-hop, IDM..... but it was so expensive and time consuming to keep up to date with every kind of music so after some years I decided to focus on house music because it was my preferred style, still don't know why, I guess it was the sexiest one :)

I currently have two types of sets, the one obviously aimed at the dancefloor which is influenced by jackin house, disco, funk, latin and some "techy" style and the other that is more suitable for beach bars and chill outs which are very popular in the East coast of Spain where I'm based these days and is composed of soulful, jazzy, deep and nu-disco vibes.

Even when I'm playing peak time stuff I try to play tunes with a minimum of quality, tracks that sound cool but that are danceable at the same time, I'd say that's my signature, playing always decent sounds and not falling desperately in the obvious stuff in order to make them dance at any cost, which is quite common now. 

A few people have told me that my sets are funny and dynamic but that they also have noticed that I never play mediocre tunes to fill my sets or only because they sound good with the rest and that all my tracks are equally good and interesting, which is the best accomplishment to me because those are exactly my intentions when it comes about djing.

I have played in all kind of bars and clubs in my area and done some gigs in Valencia, the capital city, which has an intense history of clubbing and electronic music.

These days I play at random nights in my town, Gandia and in some of the mentioned beach bars when the summer kicks in, see you there!

Raccoon records searches to experiment with and push the borders of sounds and genres to come up with sounds and melodies completely unique and original. We don’t shy away from the mainstream, but never afraid of promoting up and coming talent from all over the globe.
